Functional Tester Engineer
Can you support the team to improve quality on all levels and do you have a keen eye for quality?

The best possible customer experience starts with ensuring the quality of our services. At Knab the goal is to ensure great quality in the hands of our customers and employees. Within one of the value teams you will be building, running and owning quality for these services.
You are curious and creative. You have an eye for quality and you know how to communicate with your team members in order to improve the delivered features. You have the ability to clarify requirements and validate them against the delivered software. You understand the fundamentals of Test Automation and are willing to learn to apply this in your future work. You know that quality doesn’t come from testing alone, but is hidden in every stage of the building process. At Knab we have each other’s back!

Here’s a little taste of your challenge:

As a member of the software development team you support all phases of the software development lifecycle, from product inception to start of production and beyond;
Identify requirements and ensure that these are properly documented in the User Stories;
You communicate the testing results back to the Developers and Stakeholders;
You collaborate with other teams and members of the test guild with a desire to teach and learn from others;
Keep track of the latest technologies and practices in Testing and QA.


What you can expect from us:

A challenging position in a young, fast-growing and ambitious Business Line in Knab where you can leave your suit at home;
We like to have fun. There is no sense in coming to work every day if you don’t like the people you work with;
Freedom to take your own initiative and responsibilities;
There is time, space, budget and professional colleagues available to help you grow;
The right laptop for you;
26 holidays. And you can buy more holidays if you promise to come back;
We offer you a competitive salary, besides we are providing a public transport card and contribute to your pension scheme.


What we expect from you:
There is no set route to become a well-respected QA Engineer at Knab. But to be successful in this role, this is the kind of profile we have in mind:

Several years working experience in functional testing;
Familiar with automated testing frameworks e.g. Selenium, Specflow/Cucumber (BDD);
Familiar with API testing e.g. Postman;
Experience within Agile working environments (SCRUM/Kanban);
Experience with CICD tooling (Azure DevOps) and familiar with Cloud Platforms (AWS);
Experience with front-end and back office validation testing;
Basic programming, (DB) querying and scripting skills (C#, Typescript, JavaScript);
Experience with Salesforce is an advantage;
Experience with the domain of Lending and Mortgages is an advantage.

Note: You need to be eligible to work in the EU.

ABOUT KNAB
Knab was founded in 2012 because we think banking should be different. Simpler, smarter and more advantageous for our customers. Because we believe we can help everyone maximize their financial affairs. "Feel at ease when it comes to your finances. Every day." By combining smart technical solutions with a healthy dose of human intelligence, we create financial services that really meet your needs. Add to that some of the sublime personal service from our employees and you end up with something that's truly unique to the world of finance!

WORK WITH US!
If you come to work with us, Knab will become a significant part of your life. Therefore, we make sure the ambiance is just as exciting as your job. Check the benefits here!

WHAT DO YOU SAY?
If you still want to see more before deciding to move forward, I am happy to answer your questions and discuss.
